            "body": "This has also been discussed here:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/31737\n\nI think the easiest way to implement this without introducing breaking changes is the following:\n1. Introduce `blendfg` and `blendbg`, which applies to the background and the foreground color respectively\n2. `blend` is deprectated for backwards compatibility and works the same way as currently, but `blendbg` always takes priority if both are specified\n3. `winblend` and `pumblend` only sets the defaults for `blendbg`, when it's not specified and never toggles the blending on/off for hightlight groups that sets it\n4. `blendfg` and `blendbg` applies to all windows, both floating and regular ones\n\nNOTE. `blendbg` and `blendfg` might not be implementable in the TUI currently. But for example the [Kitty Protocol](https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/protocol-extensions/) could probably be extended with support for it. In any case it does not break anything if not supported, since it's just affects the desktop visibility through the background.",
