            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The `highlight-blend` also has some very weird behaviour of affecting things on top of it. I'm not sure if that's on purpose or not, but I don't think the `blendbg` should work that way. For example, it can turn the visual selection transparent\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b903d691-6c3e-4e38-942e-6bcf3ece390f)\nOr make the terminal background colors transparent\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e8c4545e-a15c-4fa8-9425-bde0cdfc78ed)\n\nIn both cases `winblend=1` just to enable the `blend` attribute of the custom highlight on the second line in the first example and for `FloatNormal` in the second example.",
